            "content": "<div class=\"story-content\"><p> <br>A erson who recite6 (bu'lope hundred times a day, <br>wii'1 on the Day of Resurrection, be raised with his face <br>shining like the full moon, and none can surpass him <br>in excellence on that day except one who recites this <br>Kalimah more than he. <br>Many ahaadith and ayaat confirm that ( i t 4 1  <br>is a light <br>for the heart as well as for the face. It has been observed <br>41 j <br>Ch. 11: Ahadith on Virtues of Kalimah Tayyabah 157 <br>that the pious people who are used to reciting this Kalimah <br>excessively have a sort of brightness over their faces, even <br>during their earthly life. <br>Hadith </p></div>"
